Dialogue: 0,0:02:05.10,0:02:11.56,Narrator,Narrator,0,0,0,,{\an8}Ever since Guido Mista was a child, \N he viewed life simply and lived a carefree existence.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:11.90,0:02:13.57,Narrator,Narrator,0,0,0,,He enjoyed sleeping...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:13.57,0:02:17.78,Narrator,Narrator,0,0,0,,He enjoyed watching the morning sun shining \N through tree branches as the clouds lazily drifted by...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:18.24,0:02:22.03,Narrator,Narrator,0,0,0,,He enjoyed the scent of wine \N and taste of cheese...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:22.45,0:02:26.20,Narrator,Narrator,0,0,0,,Whenever he spotted cute girls, \N he would try chatting them up, even if they shot him down.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:26.20,0:02:34.17,Narrator,Narrator,0,0,0,,If he ran out of money, he would jump anyone lined up \N in front of the local cinema who was badmouthing movie stars.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:35.00,0:02:39.63,Narrator,Narrator,0,0,0,,At times, he was beaten so badly that \N the police were forced to get involved...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:40.09,0:02:44.47,Narrator,Narrator,0,0,0,,But Mista's life up until this point \N was a happy one.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:47.10,0:02:51.06,Narrator,Narrator,0,0,0,,His carefree nature was \N occasionally mistaken for foolishness...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:51.06,0:02:59.24,Narrator,Narrator,0,0,0,,...but Mista believed it wasn't good to overthink things \N as it invited fear into one's heart.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:59.70,0:03:04.45,Narrator,Narrator,0,0,0,,When Mista turned seventeen, \N he learned from a certain incident...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:04.45,0:03:08.50,Narrator,Narrator,0,0,0,,...that everyone's destiny is predetermined. {"You'll remember you don't believe any of this fate crap." -Rolling Stone Oracle from The Jojotrix}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:08.50,0:03:12.71,Narrator,Narrator,0,0,0,,Though people tend to stall \N or take detours when they're young...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:12.71,0:03:18.63,Narrator,Narrator,0,0,0,,...they ultimately end up traveling \N the path they were destined to take.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:18.63,0:03:24.35,Narrator,Narrator,0,0,0,,One clear summer night, Mista found himself \N wandering aimlessly through the streets as he always did...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:24.80,0:03:25.81,Flashback,Girl,0,0,0,,Mista!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:25.81,0:03:27.72,Flashback,Mista,0,0,0,,Yo! Wanna have a good time?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:27.72,0:03:29.60,Flashback,Girl,0,0,0,,Sorry, we already have plans! {F}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:29.60,0:03:30.52,Flashback,Girl,0,0,0,,Ciao!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:30.52,0:03:31.31,Flashback,Mista,0,0,0,,Later!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:31.31,0:03:33.31,Flashback,Lady,0,0,0,,No! Get off me!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:33.31,0:03:35.77,Flashback,Thug,0,0,0,,I told you to cut that shit out! \N Now shut the fuck up!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:40.95,0:03:43.07,Flashback,Thug,0,0,0,,Shut the fuck up! \N Quit screaming!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:43.95,0:03:48.54,Narrator,Narrator,0,0,0,,The woman being brutalized \N inside the parked car was half naked.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:48.54,0:03:52.62,Narrator,Narrator,0,0,0,,She was bleeding from her nose and mouth \N and on the brink of losing consciousness.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:53.33,0:03:56.71,Narrator,Narrator,0,0,0,,Mista thought twice about \N getting involved, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:02.55,0:04:04.47,Flashback,Thug,0,0,0,,{\an8}Y-You fucking asshole!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:02.55,0:04:07.18,Narrator,Narrator,0,0,0,,Due to his simple personality{previously: "carefree nature" -Starfish}, \N his body acted instinctively. {Added "to". "simple personality" is kinda odd and there's probably a better way of handling it, but we haven't come up with anything. - Toa after Jules pointed the error out}{Maybe: "his body moved on reflex/reflexively.", or "his body acted on instinct." - Jules}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:07.18,0:04:10.89,Flashback,Thug,0,0,0,,You son of a bitch! \N What'd you do to our bro?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:11.43,0:04:13.10,Flashback,Thug,0,0,0,,You fucking punk!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:16.44,0:04:21.32,Narrator,Narrator,0,0,0,,No matter how close you may be to your target, \N you can never be absolutely certain that you'll hit.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:21.32,0:04:28.58,Narrator,Narrator,0,0,0,,It's all too easy to pull the trigger without \N aiming your gun properly when panicked or rushed.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:29.04,0:04:36.04,Narrator,Narrator,0,0,0,,Both shots the hooligan fired \N flew under Mista's arm and were swallowed by the darkness.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:36.04,0:04:37.25,Flashback,Thug,0,0,0,,The fuck?!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:39.21,0:04:41.46,Flashback,Thug,0,0,0,,S-Stay back! \N You hear me?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:42.59,0:04:46.22,Narrator,Narrator,0,0,0,,Three, four, five, six shots!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:46.22,0:04:49.31,Narrator,Narrator,0,0,0,,Unbelievably, they were \N all lost to the darkness.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:50.18,0:04:52.43,Narrator,Narrator,0,0,0,,His panicked friends \N began to shoot, as well.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:52.43,0:04:55.39,Narrator,Narrator,0,0,0,,However, by what can only be \N described as a miracle...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:55.39,0:04:57.77,Narrator,Narrator,0,0,0,,...Mista wasn't hit by a single bullet.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:58.19,0:05:03.49,Narrator,Narrator,0,0,0,,Meanwhile, Mista was astonished by \N his own state of silent concentration.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:03.49,0:05:04.90,Flashback,Thug,0,0,0,,What the fuck is going on?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:04.90,0:05:05.99,Flashback,Thug,0,0,0,,Wh-Who the hell is this guy?!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:05.99,0:05:07.24,Flashback,Thug,0,0,0,,Bro!
